PrecisAuthority to enter into a "SETTLEMENT AGREEMENT" between the Crown, the Province of British Columbia, the DEASE RIVER INDIAN BAND and the LIARD RIVER INDIAN BAND which provides for both the setting apart of 368.71 acres of land for the use and benefit of the Dease River Band and the making of a compensatory payment in respect of a specific claim pertaining to the right-of-way on One Mile Point Indian Reserve No. 1 for the passage of B.C. Highway No. 37.
